HEADWORD: Seating
<hw>Seat"ing</hw> <pr>(s⟦emac⟧t"⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of providing with a seat or seats; <as>as, the
<ex>seating</ex> of an audience</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of making seats; also, the material for
